  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Response to Conflict Affected IDPs and Host Communities in Tigray, Ethiopia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) to improve access to lifesaving food, nutrition, and other immediate needs; 2) to enhance awareness and provide information on referral pathways for SGBV and protection; and 3) to improve access to information and means to prevent and control the spread of Covid-19</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The response will provide in-kind food assistance to 440 HHs (2,200 individuals) monthly for three months as per the WFP standard food basket: 15 kgs of wheat flour, 1.5 kgs of pulses and 0.45 litre of vegetable oil per person per month. In addition, 1,600 children under 5 and 1,500 PLW affected by malnutrition will be provided with supplementary nutritional food of 4.5kg of Famix/ Corn Soya per person per month for three months. 4,400 bars of Soap (10 soaps of each 250g per household for 440 HHs) will be provided in the assistance packages to support improved hygiene practices and reduce transmission of Covid-19. The response will raise awareness on SGBV protection and Covid-19 in line with WHO and the Ministry of Health&#x2019;s guidance.</narrative>
  </description>
